ring, grief, and resilience among a community of medical professionals and patients at the heart of the AIDS epidemic.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 10. Jan 2022) 0aAIDS (Disease)xNursingvComic books, strips, etc. 0aHIV infectionsxNursingvComic books, strips, etc. 0aMedicinevComic books, strips, etc. 7aCOMICS & GRAPHIC NOVELS / Nonfiction / Biography & Memoir.2bisacsh1 aCzerwiec, MK.40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781637790182zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781637790182423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781637790182/original  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK